<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99535951014574></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99535951014574><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99535951014574>RE: re: trades</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99535951014574#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20521><span id= >Kelendin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 17th 4:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I suggest tailoring. You can then make yourself raw silk armor, which is very handy at low-levels, and youll make nice profit with it too (30pp for whole set) and after that you can try to make some cured silk for monks, and that is a real moneymaker, 2pp per AC. And then backpacks (10 slot) which sell for 100pp. You can also use tailoring to make some items needed in smithing, and making heady kiolas for cured silk uses brewing, so youll help 2 skills by using 1.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
